---
import GuideLayout from '../components/layout/GuideLayout.astro';
import Callout from '../components/ui/Callout.astro';
import DataTable from '../components/ui/DataTable.astro';
import JsonLd from '../components/seo/JsonLd.astro';

const headings = [
  { depth: 2, slug: 'what-are-badges', text: 'What Are Badges' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'current-badges', text: 'Current Badges' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'chat-unlock', text: 'Chat Unlock' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'future-badges', text: 'Future Badges' },
];
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Marks of Distinction"
  description="Badge guide for Ultimate Dominion. How badges work, how to earn the Adventurer and Founder badges, chat unlock requirements, and planned future badges."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Badges' }]}
  headings={headings}
>
  <JsonLd schema={{
    '@type': 'Article',
    headline: 'Marks of Distinction — Ultimate Dominion Badge Guide',
    description: 'How badges work in Ultimate Dominion: earning them, what they unlock, and what\'s planned.',
    dateModified: '2026-03-12',
  }} slot="head" />

  <h1>Marks of Distinction</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary">
    Ultimate Dominion has soulbound badge NFTs that serve as permanent, non-transferable achievements. Three badges currently exist: Adventurer (level 3, unlocks chat), Founder (level 3 during launch window), and Zone Conqueror (first 10 players to max level in a zone). Badges are earned automatically when requirements are met.
  </p>
  <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary/60 mt-2">Last updated: March 2026</p>

  <h2 id="what-are-badges">What Are Badges</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><em>Soulbound tokens — permanently attached to your character. Cannot be traded, sold, or transferred.</em></p>
  <p>
    Badges are soulbound tokens — permanently attached to your character. They cannot be traded, sold, or transferred. Each badge represents an accomplishment or status:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Badges are earned automatically when you meet the requirements.</li>
    <li>Some badges unlock game features (like chat).</li>
    <li>All badges are visible on your character profile.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="current-badges">Current Badges</h2>

  <DataTable headers={['Badge', 'Requirement', 'What It Unlocks']}>
    <tr class="hover:bg-surface/50">
      <td class="px-4 py-3">
        <span class="text-white font-bold">Adventurer</span>
      </td>
      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-primary">Reach Level 3</td>
      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-accent">Chat access</td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="hover:bg-surface/50">
      <td class="px-4 py-3">
        <span class="text-accent font-bold">Founder</span>
      </td>
      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-primary">Reach Level 3 during the launch window</td>
      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Prestige — proof you were here from the beginning</td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="hover:bg-surface/50">
      <td class="px-4 py-3">
        <span class="text-green font-bold">Zone Conqueror</span>
      </td>
      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-primary">Be among the first 10 players to reach max level in a zone</td>
      <td class="px-4 py-3 text-text-secondary">Prestige — marks you as a pioneer of that zone</td>
    </tr>
  </DataTable>

  <h2 id="chat-unlock">Chat Unlock</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><em>Chat requires Adventurer badge (level 3) — prevents spam and ensures community quality.</em></p>
  <p>
    Chat is locked behind the <strong>Adventurer badge</strong> (Level 3). This serves two purposes:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Anti-spam</strong> — creating a character takes time and effort. Requiring Level 3 prevents throwaway accounts from flooding chat.</li>
    <li><strong>Community quality</strong> — by the time you can chat, you've invested in the game. You have context, opinions, and something to say beyond noise.</li>
  </ul>

  <Callout type="tip" title="Reach Level 3 quickly">
    Fight Dire Rats and Kobolds near the spawn. Their combined XP gets you to Level 3 in a handful of fights.
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="future-badges">Future Badges</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><em>Planned: combat milestones, exploration achievements, economy markers, and community event badges.</em></p>
  <p>
    More badges are planned as the game expands. Potential categories include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Combat milestones</strong> — first PvP kill, total monsters slain, boss defeats.</li>
    <li><strong>Exploration achievements</strong> — discovering new zones, collecting all fragments.</li>
    <li><strong>Economy markers</strong> — first marketplace trade, total gold earned.</li>
    <li><strong>Community badges</strong> — event participation, contest winners.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Badge requirements and rewards will be announced as they're added.
  </p>

  <Callout type="lore">
    In the old world, marks of distinction were granted by the gods themselves — brands seared into flesh or woven into the soul. Now there are no gods to grant them. The badges come from the world itself, as if the cave is keeping score.
  </Callout>
</GuideLayout>
